  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bc2\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bc8 - \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Nomination of three names for interim president election - Vimal Weerawansa",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Voting for the interim president will be divided into three. So far the names of three have been recommended. Member of Parliament Vimal Weerawansa said that if the problems found in the social structure are not resolved, the whole country will have to face serious consequences.",
        "He mentioned the above while attending a press conference held yesterday at the office of the National Freedom Front in Colombo.",
        "The country is now facing a critical situation. Following the resignation of President Gotabaya Rajapaksa, an interim government must be established. The people of the country will never accept the government led by Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe.",
        "So far three names have been nominated to elect the President through a secret ballot in Parliament.",
        "Following the presidential election, the president should hold an all-party conference to present his plan for economic recovery.",
        "If we don't solve the basic problems that have originated in the social structure, we will have to face serious adverse consequences. Wrong news is published in the international media about the Presidential Palace and the Presidential Secretariat.",
        "We will provide unconditional support to the parties who implement the plans we present for economic recovery. All political parties should work for general consensus, excluding narrow political objectives.",
        "He said that if 225 members of Parliament do not want, there is no other alternative except going to general elections. People should understand that without solving the political crisis, the economic crisis can never be solved."
      ],
